      "rationale": "Systematic grid convergence study performed using three mesh refinement levels (coarse: 4.2M cells, medium: 12.8M cells, fine: 38.4M cells) following ASME V&V 20 Richardson extrapolation methodology. Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index: 1.8% (medium-fine pair). GCI for pressure rise: 1.2%. Observed order of accuracy 1.93, consistent with second-order spatial discretization. Time-step independence verified: NIH changes less than 0.4% between dt=2×10⁻⁵ s and dt=1×10⁻⁵ s. All production runs use fine mesh. Gradation 4 achieved.",
