      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted at FDA CDRH laboratory using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry fabricated to ±0.05 mm dimensional tolerance. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water mixture, viscosity matched to human blood at 37°C) used with characterized rheological properties. All five operating points instrumented with calibrated flow meters (±0.5%), pressure transducers (±1.5 mmHg), and hemolysis sampling protocol per ASTM F1841. Environmental conditions (temperature ±0.2°C, humidity controlled) documented. Experimental uncertainty budget fully reported. Gradation 4 achieved.",
