      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100 L) — is directly measured in the validation experiments and directly predicted by the CFD model without transformation or surrogate mapping. Secondary QoIs (pressure rise, velocity field) are mechanistically linked to the hemolysis prediction pathway. The validation QoIs are identical to the COU QoIs; no extrapolation of QoI relevance is required. Gradation 4 achieved.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
