      "rationale": "Boundary conditions applied in the CFD model (inlet velocity profile, outlet pressure, rotational speed, fluid properties) are directly mapped from the experimental measurements at each operating point. Inlet velocity profile derived from LDV measurements at the pump inlet plane. Fluid properties (density, viscosity) set to experimentally measured values for each test run. Rotational speed set to encoder-measured values (±5 RPM). Equivalency table provided mapping each CFD boundary condition to the corresponding experimental measurement with uncertainty. No assumed or estimated boundary conditions; all derived from experiment. Gradation 4 achieved.",
